Drinking variables (referring to the past 12 months): 
(1) alcohol intake in grams pure alcohol per drink day (continuous variable);
(2) annual frequency of drinking occasions (categorial with 10 levels: every day, 5-6 days a week, 3-4 days a week, 1-2 days a week, 2-3 days in a month, one day in a month, 6-11 days a year, 2-5 days a year, a single day in the past 12 months, never in the past 12 months); 
(3) the occurrence of RSOD (3 categories: no past year RSOD, infrequent RSOD = 1 to 11 episodes, at least monthly RSOD = 12 episodes or more within the past 12 months; RSOD is defined by drinking more than 40g pure alcohol in one occasion for women and 60g for men);
(4) beverage preference (3 categories: beer, wine, spirits); 
(5) drinking context (dichotomous: prefer drinking with a meal or without a meal);

Co-Variates: 
(6) Gender (dichotomous: women, men);
(7) group of age (3 categories: 18-34 years, 35-49 years, 50-65 years);
(8) educational achievement (3 categories: primary or lower secondary education, secondary education, higher education);
(9) size of place of residence (dichotomous: rural, urban area);
(10) individual harm (dichotomous: problematic alcohol use, non-problematic alcohol use based on RAPS score; at least one positive item indicated problematic alcohol use);
(11) supranational regions (4 categories: Nordic region, Central-western region, Mediterranean region, Central-eastern region)

